                    <tr>
           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">
                      <font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Graar's short guide to Valorians in HoH. This guide is not really written by me, its information gathered from the following thread: <br /><br /><a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com/forum/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=14952" target="_blank">http://necro.eqclasses.com/forum/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=14952</a><br /><br />It's the short version with my own experiences added :-)<br /><br /><b>Location</b>: Halls of Honor, one of the shrines.<br /><br /><b>Recommended level</b>: 61<br /><br /><b>Map</b>: <a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/hohonora1.gif" target="_blank">http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/hohonora1.gif</a><br /><br /><b>How to get there</b>: Zone into HoH. You'll be at GY, invis, go to one of the shrines. There are three shrines that I know of, although I've only been to two of them myself. Number 1 is at loc 2700,neg1700, number 2 is at 1500,1300.<br /><br />A few of the guards there see invis, so remember to con your way around, and avoid them easily, the place is huge. In both shrine one and two is sort of a hallway with plenty of room to kite. When you reach your shrine of choice, sit near the wall in the section with a large open spot to kite. You can't miss it.<br /><br /><b>Preparation</b>: Set up and buff at the described location. Only froggies will aggro, so you don't have to be very carefull. Get out pet, buff him and yourself up (shielding spell, manaskin and of course jboots/sow potions/run3).<br /><br />It's a very good idea to have an affliction haste item. Affl. haste III/IV or spell haste III/IV is a minimum. You can do this camp with only affl. haste II if you're using dooming, but killing sentries will be hard.<br /><br />What mobs to pull: Six mobs in each shrine, three possible types: "A Valorian Guard", "A Valorian Guardian" and "A Valorian Sentry". The sentries are what really spices up the camp, apart from them it's just another version of Katta. <br /><br />Strat is simple, pull whatever guard is still alive and closest to you. They will assist in pairs, so to break camp, pull with darkness, fd let the other guard reset, get back up and happy kiting.<br /><br /><b>Suggested spell lineup</b>:<br /><br />1) Darkness<br />2) Splurt<br />3) Dark plague/FP if you have it<br />4) Pyro/BoT if you have it<br />5) Saryrns kiss/BoD if you're level 61 or below.<br />6) Pet buff/lich/other buffs<br />7) Feign<br />8) Fear (lvl 4 version, to keep aggro if you don't have BoT)<br /><br /><b>Buffs</b>: Keep manaskin/forceshield up for safety and the mandatory shielding spell as well (magi, maelinn). <br /><br /><b>How to kill</b>: Two methods are useable. Root rot and aggro kite. I prefer aggro kiting, so that's what I'm going to write about. Root rotting is (as aggro kiting) pretty straight forward, so no explantion needed.<br /><br />This is standard aggro kiting in the section of the shrine where you buffed up. Back and forth, no problems. The guards don't run fast, and you can do this without jboots, run3 will suffice. I like to use sow potions for the extra safety when killing sentries, but it can be done without.<br /><br />One note here, about the sentries. They CANNOT be snared or rooted, but apart from that, it's just like the other guards. Drink ya sow potion when you see one spawn, and pull him with saryrns kiss (this is the dot with the longest casting time you use, and thus the hardest to stick when he is chasing you). Run like a coward druid to a corner, have him chase you there and in the last second, dash for the opposite corner. Apply a dot when you make it to the corner, wait till he's near, dash for opposite corner, rinse repeat. Send in pet when you have enough aggro for him not to kill it. Proceed until he's dead. Wee, you just woke up from camping this boring place, I almost like the sentries since they add excitement :)<br /><br />Final note, this camp is very doable without embracing for two reasons: The mobs are statics and reset when you FD and they are very slow so you can easily outrun them and retry darkness.<br /><br /><b>Loot</b>: Misc. vendorjunk, ethereal bricks you can give to your guild blacksmith, ethereal parchments (rare) and spectral parchments (very rare).<br /><br />XP: Around 5-7 pct AAxp per kill, but very steady xp and chance of spectrals makes this a very nice camp.<br /><br />Have fun, and safe hunting.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=461830" target="_blank"><b>Graar Raar</b></a> -Arch lich of Venril Sathir<br />"BLARGH! Death death death, fear me!" - Anna<br /><br />Edited for feedback, and thx to posters on the original thread who provided most of this information :-)</span id="msg"></font>
           	</td>
                    </tr>
