                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> My comments to this<br /><br />- When you kite a Sentry, even with SoW, you wont be able to cast a spell that takes longer than 3 secs before he gets to you. Spell haste items help a lot. Without SoW you wont be able to cast anything on them (unless you use pathing bugs in some rooms to exploit)<br />- Start a Sentry kite with Wake of the Dead from a nearby corpse. The WtD pet will last some good 10-15 seconds, giving you time to load several dots on the Sentry.<br />- I never got more than 6% AA per kill, at level 65. From this point of view, PoV XP is better (7-8 AA per kill from golems / razorfiends)<br />- If you're in T2 room, you might get a Guardian of Marr (the black armor guys) as a spawn. Dont worry, you can snare/root him, no problem<br />- For faster killing give your pet mage swords/fists and haste mask (if you can). It does make a difference. Just make sure you keep aggro.<br />- Keep Force Shield on you for those "ah ****" situations<br />- Keep a corpse near and use Wake of the Dead every 9 mins for that extra damage<br /><br /><center><img src="http://members.surfeu.de/srado/images/sig/iranicus_new_necro.jpg" border="0"><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12328" target="_blank">My Gear</a><br /></center></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
