                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Oh yes, I almost forgot :-)... I use a ceramic skull of decay when aggro kiting (affl haste IV). I could imagine the sentries are very hard without one. It's fairly inexpensive (I paid 2k for mine) and VERY handy (33 spell haste to detrimenal), so get one if you don't have it. Also, like iranicus, I always keep damage shield up (mana skin if you don't have forceshield).<br /><br />The xp IS lower than golems in PoV, but four factors make this a better camp IMO. All the spawns are static, so you won't have to loose a pet and /q if you somehow screw up and have to FD. Second reason is the chance of a spectral parchement. Third is the fact that there are no wanderers and fourth is that this place is hardly ever camped (on my server at least).<br /><br />I thought I remembered getting 8 pct from a mob a couple of times, but I could be wrong. However I'm very sure I've gotte 7 from some of them, although that doesn't guarantee that they give any more than 6.1 pct each. Regardless, this is my camp of choice these days, at least untill I get flagged for tactics (looking forward to trying that out) or CoD.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=461830" target="_blank"><b>Graar Raar</b></a> -Arch lich of Venril Sathir<br />"BLARGH! Death death death, fear me!" - Anna</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
